/**
 * projects-data.js
 * ------------------------------------------------------------------
 * Single source of truth for the six portfolio projects.
 *
 * WHY THIS FILE EXISTS BUT ISN'T WIRED IN (YET):
 * garden.html, galaxy.html, and formal.html each render these projects
 * with completely different markup — SVG-mounted specimens in the Garden,
 * canvas star nodes in the Atlas, editorial case-study cards in the Studio.
 * Pulling data from one shared file only pays off once each page's render
 * function is separated from its content, which means touching three
 * large, working, hand-tuned files at once — real risk of breaking a
 * visual effect for a "nice to have."
 *
 * The safer path: keep this file as the single place you edit project
 * facts (title, years, tags, description), and update each HTML file's
 * hard-coded copy to match it by hand for now. When you're ready to
 * actually wire it in, each page just needs a small render function
 * that maps over PROJECTS and builds its existing DOM/SVG structure —
 * happy to build that with you when you want to take it on.
 * ------------------------------------------------------------------
 */

